---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Methodology">
  <section class="page-intro"><div class="eyebrow">How this works</div><h1>Knowledge with a visible chain of evidence</h1><p>Transcripts are processed locally, concepts are proposed by Codex in a constrained schema, and reviewed material is published only when every item points to real transcript segments and timestamps.</p></section>
  <section class="method-grid">
    <article><span>01</span><h2>Collect</h2><p>Retrieve video metadata and available timed captions without publishing media files.</p></article>
    <article><span>02</span><h2>Extract</h2><p>Codex proposes concepts, aliases, relationships, and evidence using stable transcript segment IDs.</p></article>
    <article><span>03</span><h2>Review</h2><p>A maintainer accepts, merges, corrects, or rejects proposals in version-controlled files.</p></article>
    <article><span>04</span><h2>Trace</h2><p>The site calculates source windows and links every published insight to the corresponding video moment.</p></article>
  </section>
  <section class="policy-callout"><h2>Limitations</h2><p>Captions and generated analysis can be wrong. Visual demonstrations remain labeled as transcript-inferred until a reviewer verifies the footage. This project is independent and does not imply creator endorsement.</p></section>
</BaseLayout>

